Former Arsenal star Kevin Campbell has revealed his opinion that Gabriel Martinelli possesses similar characteristics to Brazilian legend Ronaldo. Versatile attacker Martinelli of course made the move to the Emirates in the summer of 2019, from his home country of Brazil. With Arsenal having also secured the high-profile additions of the likes of Dani Ceballos, Kieran Tierney and Nicolas Pepe, though, Martinelli’s arrival slipped somewhat under the radar. The campaign that ensued, however, saw the South American prodigy stand out as arguably the most consistent of the Gunners’ batch of summer signings. Despite his tender years, Martinelli already looks a genuine star in the making. The youngster possesses all of the desirable traits of a modern attacker, combining touch, stature, poise, pace, the ability to beat opposing defenders and, perhaps most significantly of all, a real eye for goal. This allowed Martinelli to directly contribute to a remarkable 10 goals across 9 appearances between the League Cup and Europa League in 2019/20. In addition, crucially, he began to carry his goalscoring exploits onto the Premier League stage earlier this year, with key strikes versus the likes of Sheffield United and Chelsea. Fill in the blank… My favourite Gabriel Martinelli moment so far is _________ @g_martinelli01 pic.twitter.com/30vfn4RFIi — Arsenal (@Arsenal) October 12, 2020 As such, it no doubt came as a major blow to club and player alike when, on the back of football’s return in June, word was forthcoming that Martinelli was set for a considerable spell on the sidelines. The 19-year-old was forced under the knife, to fix a lingering knee problem. In turn, he has now not taken to the pitch for a single appearance since all the way back in February. <img src="https://i1.wp.com/www.101greatgoals.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/GettyImages-1178827505-1024x705.jpg?resize=1024%2C705&#038;ssl=1" data-recalc-dims="1" data-lazy-src="https://i1.wp.com/www.101greatgoals.com/wp-con